Sec. 165.027. ENTRY POWER. (a) A representative of the
commission, including a member of the commission, is entitled to
enter the premises of any person for the purpose of inspecting swine
or the heating or cooking equipment required by this subchapter or
for the purpose of performing another duty under this subchapter.
(b) A person may not refuse to permit an inspection authorized
by this subchapter.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1430, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

